# Changelog Guidelines

This project uses [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/) format.

## When to Update

Update CHANGELOG.md when:
- Adding new features or functionality
- Making breaking changes
- Fixing bugs
- Deprecating features
- Removing features
- Making security improvements

## Entry Format

Add entries under the `[Unreleased]` section using these categories:

- **Added** - new features
- **Changed** - changes to existing functionality
- **Deprecated** - soon-to-be removed features
- **Removed** - removed features
- **Fixed** - bug fixes
- **Security** - vulnerability fixes

## Writing Style

```markdown
### Added
- Brief, clear description of change (context if needed)
```

- Start with a verb (Add, Fix, Update, Remove, Improve)
- Keep entries concise but informative
- Group related changes together
- Reference issue/PR numbers when applicable: `(#123)`

## Release Process

When releasing a new version:
1. Move `[Unreleased]` entries to new version section: `## [X.Y.Z] - YYYY-MM-DD`
2. Create new empty `[Unreleased]` section at top
3. Update comparison links at bottom of file
4. Bump version in `package.json` to match
